Controller should NOT contain business logic
Service should contain business logic


ervice layer contains business logic of the application.

Example Business Logic:

In Student App:

Validate student age
Check if student already exists
Calculate grade
Format name
Apply rules
Call multiple repositories
Transactions

These should be in Service, not Controller.

-----------
This class is a Service
Create its object
Store it in Spring Container
Manage it

This object is called a Bean.
---------------
USING SERVICE IN CONTROLLER -> Dependency Injection


-----------------------------
Service layer usually handles:

Business logic
Validation
Calculations
Transactions
Calling multiple repositories
Error handling
Data processing

Controller should only:

Receive request
Call service
Return response

-------
Service layer handles:

Validation
Rules
Conditions

